<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Forbidden | VulnLab</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">

        <div class="navbar">
            <h1>VulnLab</h1>
            <div class="navbar-links">
                <a href="/dashboard">Dashboard</a>
                <a href="/learn">📚 Learn</a>
                <a href="/auth/logout">Logout</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="danger">
            <h2>🚫 403 — Forbidden</h2>
            <p>You tried to access Order #<%= order_id %>
            </p>
            <p>That order belongs to User #<%= order_owner %>
            </p>
            <p>You are User #<%= session_user %>
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>The secure route <strong>caught and blocked this attack!</strong></p>
        </div>

        <div class="learn-card">
            <h3>What just happened?</h3>
            <p>The secure route ran this check:</p>
            <div class="code-block">
                <p>if (order.user_id !== req.session.user_id) {"{"}</p>
                <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;return res.status(403).render('forbidden');</p>
                <p>{"}"}</p>
            </div>
            <br />
            <p>This returned <strong>true</strong> — you don't own this order — so the server blocked access instead of
                leaking data.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="learn-card">
            <h3>Vulnerable vs Secure</h3>
            <p>🔴 <code>/orders/<%= order_id %></code> → leaks data to anyone</p>
            <p>🟢 <code>/secure/orders/<%= order_id %></code> → blocked unauthorized access</p>
        </div>

        <hr class="divider" />
        <a href="/dashboard">← Back to Dashboard</a>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;
        <a href="/learn">📚 Learn about IDOR</a>

        <div class="footer">⚠ VulnLab — For educational purposes only</div>
    </div>
</body>

</html>